<p>The three medals are used in context of the overall <em>Hall of Fame</em>. In other words: the universal winners, disregarding the challenge, are rewarded with the corresponding medals in the desired <em>Hall of Fame</em>. Naturally, the first place has the honor of receiving the gold medal, while place two and three get ahold of the silver and bronze one.</p>

